movies.title: Pope Francis: A Man of His Word
movies.title_english: Pope Francis: A Man of His Word
movies.title_long: Pope Francis: A Man of His Word (2018)
movies.summary: "Pope Francis - A Man of His Word" is intended to be a personal journey with Pope Francis, rather than a biographical documentary about him. The pope's ideas and his message are central to this documentary, which sets out to present his work of reform and his answers to today's global questions.

movies.title: Lou Andreas-Salomé, The Audacity to be Free
movies.title_english: Lou Andreas-Salomé, The Audacity to be Free
movies.title_long: Lou Andreas-Salomé, The Audacity to be Free (2016)
movies.summary: Lou Andreas-Salomé, the woman who enraptured 19th century Europe's greatest minds, recounts her life to Ernst Pfeiffer in this German film directed by Cordula Post-Kablutz. A published novelist, poet and essayist, Salomé's desire to live a life free from convention scandalized society but spurred genius and passion in others, including Friedrich Nietzsche, Paul Rée and her lover, the poet Rainer Maria Rilke. Under the tutelage of Sigmund Freud, she became the first female psychoanalyst.

movies.title: George Harrison: Living in the Material World
movies.title_english: George Harrison: Living in the Material World
movies.title_long: George Harrison: Living in the Material World (2011)
movies.summary: George Harrison first became known to the world as "The Quiet Beatle" of the Fab Four, but there was far more to his life than simply being a part of The Beatles. This film explores the life and career of this seminal musician, philanthropist, film producer and amateur race car driver who grew to make his own mark on the world. Through his music, archival footage and the memories of friends and family, Harrison's deep spirituality and humanity are explored in his singular life as he took on artistic challenges and important causes as only he could.
